President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. These individuals include Nina M. Archabal, who is being appointed as a member of the Cultural Property Advisory Committee. Archabal is the Director Emerita of the Minnesota Historical Society and has received numerous awards for her work in historic preservation. Barbara Bluhm-Kaul is also being appointed as a member of the Cultural Property Advisory Committee. She is a trustee of The Art Institute in Chicago and has loaned works from her collection to major museums around the world. Regina Blye is being appointed as a member of the Architectural and Transportation Barriers Compliance Access Board. She is the Executive Director of the Texas State Independent Living Council and has been involved in advocating for the rights of Texans with disabilities. Cindy Campbell is being appointed as a member of the American Battle Monuments Commission. She is currently the Vice President for Community Relations and Media Affairs at the Fisher House Foundation and previously served in the Navy for 30 years.